    {
      "id": "overview",
      "title": "Role Overview",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "Mobile interviews assess platform-specific knowledge (iOS/Android), app architecture, performance optimization, and general programming skills. Expect coding challenges, design discussions, and platform deep dives."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**What interviewers assess:**\n\n- Platform expertise (iOS/Swift or Android/Kotlin)\n- Mobile architecture patterns (MVVM, Clean Architecture)\n- UI/UX implementation skills\n- Performance and memory management\n- App lifecycle and background processing"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "format",
      "title": "Common Interview Format",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Typical mobile interview loop:**\n\n1. **Recruiter screen** (30 min)\n2. **Technical phone screen** (45-60 min) - Coding or platform questions\n3. **Onsite/Virtual loop** (4-5 hours):\n   - Platform-specific deep dive\n   - Coding/algorithm round\n   - Mobile system design\n   - Behavioral round"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "content": {
            "text": "Be ready to discuss trade-offs between native and cross-platform approaches. Know when each makes sense."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "answer-frameworks",
      "title": "How to Structure Your Answers",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "header",
          "content": {
            "text": "How to Structure Your Answers"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "Great Mobile Engineer interview answers follow proven structures. These frameworks help you give complete, compelling responses that cover everything interviewers want to hear."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Pro tip:** Don't memorize scripts. Learn these frameworks so you can adapt them to any question. Interviewers can tell when answers are rehearsed word-for-word."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Behavioral Questions**"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "Use the **STAR with leadership lens** framework:"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "checklist",
          "content": {
            "title": "Key Elements to Cover",
            "items": [
              {
                "id": "behavioral-elem-0",
                "text": "Why you stepped up (not because you had to)",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "behavioral-elem-1",
                "text": "How you built alignment without authority",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "behavioral-elem-2",
                "text": "Specific influence tactics used",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "behavioral-elem-3",
                "text": "How you handled resistance",
                "required": false
              },
              {
                "id": "behavioral-elem-4",
                "text": "Measurable outcome",
                "required": false
              },
              {
                "id": "behavioral-elem-5",
                "text": "What you'd do differently",
                "required": false
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Time allocation:** Situation: 15%, Task: 10%, Action: 55%, Result: 20%"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "quote",
          "content": {
            "text": "Example: \"Tell me about a time you had to lead a project without formal authority.\""
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Technical Questions**"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "Use the **Define -> Examples -> Trade-offs -> Business context** framework:"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "checklist",
          "content": {
            "title": "Key Elements to Cover",
            "items": [
              {
                "id": "technical-elem-0",
                "text": "Clear definition of both types",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "technical-elem-1",
                "text": "Real-world example (spam filter, medical diagnosis)",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "technical-elem-2",
                "text": "When to prioritize Type I (false positive) avoidance",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "technical-elem-3",
                "text": "When to prioritize Type II (false negative) avoidance",
                "required": false
              },
              {
                "id": "technical-elem-4",
                "text": "How sample size affects both",
                "required": false
              },
              {
                "id": "technical-elem-5",
                "text": "How to explain to product managers",
                "required": false
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Be ready for follow-ups:** Expect: 'How do you set alpha level for an experiment?' or 'What's the relationship to statistical power?' or 'Give me an example from a project.'"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "quote",
          "content": {
            "text": "Example: \"Explain the difference between Type I and Type II errors. When might you prioritize one over the other?\""
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Culture Fit Questions**"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "Use the **Authenticity-First** framework:"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "checklist",
          "content": {
            "title": "Key Elements to Cover",
            "items": [
              {
                "id": "culture-elem-0",
                "text": "Why you noticed the gap (shows awareness)",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "culture-elem-1",
                "text": "Why you chose to act vs. escalate (judgment)",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "culture-elem-2",
                "text": "How you balanced this with your actual responsibilities",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "culture-elem-3",
                "text": "The outcome and what you learned",
                "required": false
              },
              {
                "id": "culture-elem-4",
                "text": "Whether you'd approach it differently now",
                "required": false
              },
              {
                "id": "culture-elem-5",
                "text": "How it shaped your view of ownership",
                "required": false
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Authenticity check:** Before answering, ask yourself: Would I do this again? If you genuinely wouldn't, pick a different example where you felt energized by the ownership."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "quote",
          "content": {
            "text": "Example: \"Tell me about a time you took on something outside your job description because it needed to be done.\""
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Curveball & Estimation Questions**"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "Use the **Estimate container volume -> Estimate object volume -> Divide -> Sanity check** framework:"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "checklist",
          "content": {
            "title": "Key Elements to Cover",
            "items": [
              {
                "id": "curveball-elem-0",
                "text": "Estimate bus dimensions (state as assumption)",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "curveball-elem-1",
                "text": "Calculate bus volume in cubic feet",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "curveball-elem-2",
                "text": "Estimate golf ball diameter and volume",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "curveball-elem-3",
                "text": "Account for packing efficiency (~60-70%)",
                "required": false
              },
              {
                "id": "curveball-elem-4",
                "text": "Do the division",
                "required": false
              },
              {
                "id": "curveball-elem-5",
                "text": "Sanity check: 'Does this feel reasonable?'",
                "required": false
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Stay composed:** Say: 'I'll estimate this step by step and state my assumptions as I go.' This signals you know what they're looking for and buys you thinking time."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "quote",
          "content": {
            "text": "Example: \"How many golf balls fit in a school bus?\""
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Remember:** The best answers are specific, structured, and show self-awareness. Use these frameworks as guides, but adapt them to your actual experiences."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "competencies",
      "title": "Key Competencies",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "checklist",
          "content": {
            "title": "Technical Areas to Review",
            "items": [
              {
                "id": "c1",
                "text": "Platform fundamentals (iOS: UIKit/SwiftUI, Android: Jetpack)",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "c2",
                "text": "App architecture patterns",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "c3",
                "text": "Networking and offline support",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "c4",
                "text": "Memory management and performance profiling",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "c5",
                "text": "App lifecycle and state management",
                "required": true
              },
              {
                "id": "c6",
                "text": "Testing strategies (unit, UI, integration)",
                "required": true
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "mistakes-to-avoid",
      "title": "Mistakes to Avoid",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "header",
          "content": {
            "text": "Common Interview Mistakes to Avoid"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "Even strong Mobile Engineer candidates make these mistakes in interviews. Knowing what to avoid is just as important as knowing what to do."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Behavioral Question Mistakes**"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "Taking all credit (saying 'I' too much, never 'we')"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "Focusing on the WHAT instead of the HOW of leadership"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "Describing coercion as influence"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "Skipping the outcome or metrics"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Technical Question Mistakes**"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "Only textbook definition without examples"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "No business context for trade-offs"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "Confusing the two types"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "Over-complicating the explanation"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Culture Fit Mistakes**"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "Framing it as a burden you had to bear"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "Taking on things to show off rather than because they mattered"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "No clear impact or outcome from the extra work"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "Implying you only do this when asked or incentivized"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Curveball Question Mistakes**"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "Freezing or saying 'I don't know'"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "Guessing a random number without showing work"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "Getting defensive when pushed on assumptions"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "warning",
          "content": {
            "text": "Over-engineering the calculation"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Remember:** Interviewers notice patterns. If you catch yourself heading toward one of these mistakes, pause, acknowledge it, and redirect. Self-awareness goes a long way."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
